{"questionId":"27002664","questionHtml":"<p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f'\\left( x \\right) = \\frac{{8x}}{{\\sqrt {2{x^2} + 1} }}\">\n  <msup>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mo>′</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>8</mn>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>x</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>. Given that&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( 0 \\right) = 5\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n</math></span>, find <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to integrate&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"u = 2{x^2} + 1 \\Rightarrow \\frac{{{\\text{d}}u}}{{{\\text{d}}x}} = 4x\">\n  <mi>u</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\int {\\frac{{8x}}{{\\sqrt {2{x^2} + 1} }}} {\\text{d}}x = \\int {\\frac{2}{{\\sqrt u }}} {\\text{d}}u\">\n  <mo>∫</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>8</mn>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msqrt>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </msqrt>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>d</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>∫</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <msqrt>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n        </msqrt>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>d</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>u</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>EITHER</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = 4\\sqrt u \\left( { + C} \\right)\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mi>u</mi>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>C</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = 4\\sqrt {2{x^2} + 1} \\left( { + C} \\right)\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>C</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>THEN</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct substitution into <strong>their</strong> integrated function (must have <em>C</em>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"5 = 4 + C \\Rightarrow C = 1\">\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = 4\\sqrt {2{x^2} + 1}&nbsp; + 1\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27002664","referenceCode":"SPM.1.SL.TZ0.4","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Let f ′ ( x ) = 8 x 2 x 2 + 1 . Given that f ( 0 ) = 5 , find f ( x ) .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"4","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.10—Indefinite integration, reverse chain, by substitution"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}